The paper discusses the challenges of information-intensive software engineering and proposes an approach to address these challenges by integrating a flexible query mechanism into the development environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for combining information from different sources, flexibly presenting collected information, and automatically acting on collected information, which are all related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of scripts to extend the approach, which is related to Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of version repositories and issue trackers, which are related to Databases (cs.DB) sub-category.
